title: Cowboys are coming to Cairns
text:
Cowboys co-captains Johnathan Thurston and Matt Scott to visit Cairns next Sunday by: ON THEIR WAY: NRL Premiership-winning co-captains Matt Scott and Johnathan Thurston will visit Cairns with a group of their teammates next Sunday. PICTURE: CAMERON SPENCER/GETTY Source: Getty Images 
NORTH Queensland Cowboys superstar Johnathan Thurston will visit Cairns next Sunday. 
In a statement on Friday afternoon, the club confirmed premiership-winning co-captains Thurston and Matt Scott would be among a group of players flying to Cairns, Mt Isa and Mackay on October 18. 
While specific details remain unclear, a Cairns Regional Council spokeswoman said “further details, including times and location will be confirmed with the Cowboys in coming days”. 
The club will also be bringing the Provan-Summons Trophy on the tour. 
Read more in the Weekend Post .
